# AI Working State
Last updated: 2026-06-26

This file holds ONLY globally-useful state: the single thing most recently/
currently worked on (with a pointer to its full state), an index of the per-spec
state files, the release log, and the cross-cutting decisions/preferences.

**Detailed, spec-scoped working state lives in `state/<track>.md`** — one file
per spec, each linked from its spec's header. Read AI.state first; then read only
the `state/` file for the track you're touching. See CLAUDE.md "AI working state"
for the protocol (how to keep this single-latest and where new notes go).

## Latest
RELEASED **v2.8.2** (2026-06-26, tag on e16a687). CRITICAL HA-freeze fix + noise
cut. (1) Card 0.3.18 configure STORM: _maybeConfigure re-sent `configure` on every
card re-instantiation (HA recreates cards freely + on reconnect) → daemon
re-published companion → new hass state → card recreated → loop, flooding POST
/api/events/ha_lua_command until the frontend WS dropped (code 3 "Connection
lost") and the UI froze. Fix: reconcile against the already-published companion
(_companionConfigured: window.sensors+presets), only configure on real change;
also catch fire-and-forget callApi/callService so blips don't spam uncaught
rejections. Commit e44bc5a. (2) enhanced_climate.lua publish_companion now skips
unchanged companion writes (was a no-op state_changed + recorder row per companion
PER MINUTE — the "refreshed companion" debug spam); PUBLISH_HEARTBEAT 5m keeps
self-heal since published states aren't integration-backed and Seed doesn't prune
the mirror. Commit fe57c8f. Full detail: **`state/enhanced-climate.md`**.

